anings":["Originally a variant of   Helen  , although now no longer associated with that name. Initial <i>H-</i> tended to be added and dropped rather capriciously, leading to many doublets (  compare for example  Esther   and   Hester  ). It is also sometimes used as a short form of   Eleanor  , to which, however, it is unrelated."]},{"name":"Hellen","meanings":["Of uncertain derivation, perhaps an altered form of Irish   Kelan  , or a shortened form of the Scottish surname <i>McKellen</i> (Gaelic <i>Mac Ailein</i> ‘son of Alan’ or <i>Mac Cailein</i> ‘son of Colin’)."]}]},{"name":"Ier","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["from Yiddish <i>ber</i> ‘bear’, probably influenced by the early medieval European practice of giving animal names to people. It is often paired with   Dov   in order to provide a Hebrew name in certain rituals."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Hellin Ier DE WAVRIN was born in 1190, in Wavrin, Nord, France as the son of Sibylle de CROISILLES. He married Elisabeth de Morialmé in 1211. They were the parents of at least 1 son and 3 daughters. In 1214, at the age of 24, his occupation is listed as chevalier. He died on 13 March 1223, at the age of 33."},"et":{"1190–13 mars 1223":"1190–13. märts 1223","1190–1223":"1190–1223","1190–1264":"1190–1264","1215–1283":"1215–1283","1220–Female":"1220–Surnud","1235–1284":"1235–1284","–1253":"–1253","1176–1236":"1176–1236","1190":"1190","1176":"1176","1253":"1253","1220":"1220","1264":"1264","1284":"1284","1283":"1283","du 1198 au 1219":"1198 kuni 1219","1215":"1215","circa 1220":"umbes 1220","1214":"1214","1236":"1236","1235":"1235","1223":"1223","1211":"1211","13 mars 1223":"13. märts 1223","Wavrin - Nord - France":"Wavrin, Nord, Nord-Pas-de-Calais, Prantsusmaa","Wavrin, Nord, France":"Wavrin, Nord, Prantsusmaa"},"fi":{"1190–13 mars 1223":"1190–13. maaliskuuta 1223","1190–1223":"1190–1223","1190–1264":"1190–1264","1215–1283":"1